# PicoClaw Setup Commands (Windows)

**Note:** This setup includes custom additions not in the original picoclaw repository:
- `pkg/channels/web.go` - HTTP REST API channel for web interface communication
- `web-interface/` folder - Web UI and Electron desktop app
- `build-windows.bat` - Windows build script with workspace embedding

---

## Prerequisites
Install Go 1.21+, Node.js 18+, and Git before starting.
  Go:     https://go.dev/dl/
  Node:   https://nodejs.org/
  Git:    https://git-scm.com/

---

## 1. Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/sipeed/picoclaw.git
cd picoclaw

## 2. Build the binary
.\build-windows.bat
  (or: go build -o build\picoclaw.exe .\cmd\picoclaw\)

## 3. Run first-time onboarding
.\build\picoclaw.exe onboard
  -> Creates config at %USERPROFILE%\.picoclaw\config.json
  -> Edit that file to:
     1. Add your API key (required)
     2. Enable web channel: set channels.web.enabled = true
     3. Set channels.web.port = 18790 (default, matches api-server)

## 4. Start the gateway
.\build\picoclaw.exe gateway

## 5. Start the web interface (second terminal)
cd web-interface
npm install
npm start
  -> Open http://localhost:3000 in your browser

---

## Optional: Electron desktop app (auto-starts gateway)
cd web-interface
npm install
npm run electron

## Optional: Build a distributable Windows installer
cd web-interface
npm run dist:win
  -> Produces installer in web-interface\dist\

## Optional: Run tests
go test ./...
